Practical No. 1 : Configure Routers
Aim 
a) OSPF MD5 authentication.

Steps:
Step 1: Configure Router Interfaces

Assign IP addresses to router interfaces.

Enable interfaces.

Router> enable
Router# configure terminal
Router(config)# interface g0/0
Router(config-if)# ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
Router(config-if)# no shutdown
Router(config-if)# exit

Repeat for all interfaces between OSPF neighbors.

Step 2: Configure OSPF with MD5 Authentication

Router(config)# router ospf 1
Router(config-router)# network 192.168.1.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
Router(config-router)# exit

Enable MD5 authentication on interface:

Router(config)# interface g0/0
Router(config-if)# ip ospf authentication message-digest
Router(config-if)# ip ospf message-digest-key 1 md5 cisco123
Router(config-if)# exit

Step 3: Verify OSPF Neighbors

Router# show ip ospf neighbor
Router# show running-config